<subSubSection id="C3750A9EFF99FFAEFF7CC61CFF32C48D" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD05915FF99FFAEFF7CC61CFF18C441" blockId="1.[151,685,223,285]" box="[151,235,259,285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">
(
<figureCitation id="13544590FF99FFAEFF4BC61CFF13C441" box="[160,224,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[276,1312,921,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-302@1.[276,1312,921,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole horvati Sivec &amp; Harper, 2008, female. a. terminalia, ventral view; b. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD05915FF99FFAEFF7CC654FF32C48D" blockId="1.[151,1437,331,898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF99FFAEFF7CC654FF06C439" bold="true" box="[151,245,331,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Female.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity id="4C97F4F0FF99FFAEFE56C654FDB7C43A" box="[445,580,331,358]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="7.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" unit="mm" value="7.55" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="7.3">7.3–7.8 mm</quantity>
(n=2). Posterior margin of sternum 7 produced into an elongate, sclerotized subgenital plate, the plate generally triangular with nipple-like distal half, about one third width of the segment 7, and overhanging ½ length of sternum 9 (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF99FFAEFDB0C68CFD12C4F2" box="[603,737,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[276,1312,921,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-302@1.[276,1312,921,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole horvati Sivec &amp; Harper, 2008, female. a. terminalia, ventral view; b. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Figs. 1a–1b</figureCitation>
). Sternum 8 mostly brown except for pale lateral margins (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF99FFAEFA84C68CFF40C48D" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[276,1312,921,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-302@1.[276,1312,921,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole horvati Sivec &amp; Harper, 2008, female. a. terminalia, ventral view; b. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
