<subSubSection id="C3750A9EFF99FFAEFF2CC574FA94C6DE" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD05915FF99FFAEFF2CC574FA94C6DE" blockId="1.[151,1437,331,898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF99FFAEFF2CC574FEC8C7D9" bold="true" box="[199,315,619,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Remarks.</emphasis>
Three females were originally identified and described as the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F2296FF99FFAEFBB7C573FB38C7D9" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Harper" authorityYear="2008" box="[1116,1227,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvati">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF99FFAEFBB7C573FB38C7D9" box="[1116,1227,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">R. horvati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because they were collected at the same province as the 
<typeStatus id="54D4E7B7FF99FFAEFDDAC590FD64C7F5" box="[561,663,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">holotype</typeStatus>
. The present female is positively associated as mating pairs. The original female from 
<collectingRegion id="49AB97F7FF99FFAEFEBDC5ACFDE9C791" box="[342,538,691,717]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Sichuan Province</collectingRegion>
is superficially similar to this female, however, the subgenital plate of the former forms an isosceles triangle with wider base and an acute distal point (fig. 33.6, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE24E4FF99FFAEFBE0C5C8FB3AC7AD" author="Sivec, I. &amp; Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T." box="[1035,1225,727,754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref2781" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T. (2008) Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia, 64, 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="2008">Sivec et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), whereas for what we consider as the true females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F2296FF99FFAEFDF0C5E3FD78C649" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Harper" authorityYear="2008" box="[539,651,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvati">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF99FFAEFDF0C5E3FD78C649" box="[539,651,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">R. horvati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the base is constricted and the distal half is nipple-like with an obtuse apex. The shape is consistent between the females of 
<collectingRegion id="49AB97F7FF99FFAEFD00C400FCC0C665" box="[747,819,799,825]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Gansu</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49AB97F7FF99FFAEFC82C400FC34C665" box="[873,967,799,825]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
. Therefore, we consider the differences of subgenital plate are interspecific. We conclude the 
<specimenCount id="9D69929CFF99FFAEFD3FC45CFC98C601" box="[724,875,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" type="female">three females</specimenCount>
originally associated with the 
<typeStatus id="54D4E7B7FF99FFAEFB2EC45CFAD4C601" box="[1221,1319,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F2296FF99FFAEFAA6C45BFF32C6DD" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Harper" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvati">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF99FFAEFAA6C45BFF32C6DD" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">R. horvati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were erroneous and that those females were treated herein as an unidentified female in this species group.
</paragraph>
